# Code
```java []
class Solution {
    public int maxArea(int[] height) {
        int maxWater = 0;
        
        // start from the outside, and iterate inwards
        int leftBound = 0;
        int rightBound = height.length - 1;

        while(leftBound < rightBound) {
            // compare current height and width with current champion area
            int h = Math.min(height[leftBound], height[rightBound]);
            int w = rightBound - leftBound;
            maxWater = Math.max(maxWater, h * w);

            // adjust smaller bounds, as width shrinks, height must increase
            if(height[leftBound] < height[rightBound]) {
                leftBound++;
            } else {
                rightBound--;
            }
        }
        return maxWater;
    }
}
```
